<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-053-213 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 311 245</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Sept 25 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IDB Communications gets new int'l authority. (IDB CommunicationsGroup Inc. receives permission from FCC to provide internationallong distance service)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   IDB Communications Group Inc. (Services).andO;Ticker:    IDBX.andO;Topic:     United States. Federal Communications CommissionLong-distance telephone servicesInternational Communications.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>****IDB COMMUNICATIONS GETS NEW INT'L AUTHORITY 09/25/91 WASHINGTON, D.C.,andO;U.S.A., 1991 SEP 25 (NB) -- The Federal Communications Commission has giventhe IDB Communications Group authority to offer international long distanceservice to 72 countries.andP;  IDB had previously been only a wholesaler of longdistance time to other companies, and had signed access to its Sovietcircuits to Sprint.andM;The  FCC also gave IDB 30 more circuits over Intelsat, the internationalsatellite organization, to the Soviet Union.andP;  Previously, 24 temporarycircuits had been granted to IDB on Intersputnik, the Soviet satellitesystem.andM;IDB said it should have switched-services available to all 72 countries bythe end of the year.andM;Chairman Jeffrey P. Sudikoff said in a press release that: &quot;Clearance toprovide service to the Soviet Union was a highly visible way for us to launchour international long distance services.andP;  This new award is even moresignificant, as it more than doubles our circuit capacity to the USSR, andallows us to access the rest of the world faster than we anticipated.&quot;andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19910925/Press Contact: David Walke, for IDB, 212-986-5900)</TEXT></DOC>